Maarten Arens Judoka
Home
Judoka
Maarten Arens
Judo career
Maarten Arens
Country: Netherlands | Born: 20 May 1972 (51 years)
Maarten Arens was European Champion in 1995 and successful coach of the Netherlands since 2005. Arens won Olympic medals as a coach with Ruben Houkes and Henk Grol and World titles with Guillaume Elmont, Dennis van der Geest and Ruben Houkes as well as a handful of European titles. He is one of the longest seeding national coaches in the world. As an athlete he became European Champion in Birmingham in 1995 and competed at the Sydney Olympic Games. Maarten is quadrupple Dutch champion. He claimed gold at the Tournoi de Paris in 2000,
Judo career

Leon Beeren Judoka
Home
Judoka
Leon Beeren
Judo career
Leon BEEREN
NED
JudoInside.com
Leon Beeren
Country: Netherlands | Born: 6 July 1982 (41 years)
Judoka Leon Beeren won a bronze medal at the Dutch Cadet Championships Maastricht in 1998 in the category O81kg. He claimed a bronze medal at the Dutch Championships U20 Groningen in 1998 at U100kg. Beeren clinched a bronze medal at the Dutch Championships U20 in 2001 in the category U100kg. He took the bronze medal at the Dutch Championships U20 Maastricht in 2000 in the weight class U100kg. Beeren captured a bronze medal at the Dutch Team Championships U20 Beverwijk in 2001 at O90kg.
Judo career

Martin van den Berg Judoka
Home
Judoka
Martin van den Berg
Judo career
Martin VAN DEN BERG
NED
JudoInside.com
Martin van den Berg
Country: Netherlands | Born: 24 February 1976 (47 years)
Martin van den Berg was Dutch judo champion in 2000. The powerhouse won various Dutch medals. As junior he won bronze at the World Championships. As senior he finished 7th in 1999 U100kg. He won World Cup medals in Warsaw, Den Bosch, Moscow and Rotterdam.
Judo career

Remy Bindadin Judoka
Home
Judoka
Remy Bindadin
Judo career
Remy BINDADIN
NED
JudoInside.com
Remy Bindadin
Country: Netherlands | Born: 15 June 1981 (42 years)
Remy Bindadin from Netherlands took a gold medal at Dutch junior Team Championships in 1996. He claimed a gold medal at Dutch Chs Cadet Teams ‘s-Hertogenbosch in 1996. Remy ranked third at International Masters Bremen U18 in 1998. He finished with gold at Beker der Kempen Herentals U19 in 1995. Bindadin clinched a bronze medal at Dutch cadet Championships U17 Dieren in 1997. He secured bronze at Dutch junior Championships Groningen in 1998. He captured a bronze medal at Dutch Cadet Championships Zwolle in 1996 and he won a bronze medal at Dutch Championships U18 Born in 1995.
Judo career

Nicky Boontje Judoka
Home
Judoka
Nicky Boontje
Judo career
Nicky Boontje
Country: Netherlands | Born: 31 March 1978 (45 years)
Nicky Boontje was a talented Dutch judoka who won bronze at European Junior championships in 1995 and 1996 and bronze at World Championships in 1996 U61kg. She won 8 Dutch senior medals. She won the Dutch and Polish Open in 2001. Later she moved to Gambia as owner of a hostel.

Edith Bosch Judoka
Home
Judoka
Edith Bosch
Judo career
Edith Bosch
Country: Netherlands | Born: 31 May 1980 (43 years)
Edith Bosch is 2005 World Champion and triple Olympic medallist 2004-2012. Bosch retired in April 2013 with a unique European team title. She is four times European champion. She won 15 World Cups and 45 World Cup medals. Nickname: Bambi. Bosch was double World Junior champion. She won 15 World Cups including the Tournoi de Paris. She was coached by Chris de Korte.

Lars Bosman Judoka
Home
Judoka
Lars Bosman
Judo career
Lars BOSMAN
NED
JudoInside.com
Lars Bosman
Country: Netherlands | Born: 12 July 1971 (52 years)
Dutch judoka Lars Bosman won seven Dutch Championships medals. He won the title twice as cadet judoka fighting for his teams SV Helsdingen (Barneveld) and Judo Ryu Nijmegen with whom he won the national team title as well. In 1987 he won EYOD silver. Loves diving.

Nicolas Brisson Judoka
Home
Judoka
Nicolas Brisson
Judo career
Nicolas Brisson
Country: France | Born: 10 November 1981 (41 years)
Nicolas Brisson is 2008 French Champion. He was born in The Netherlands. Brisson won international medals from 2007-2016. Silver at 2009 French Championships.

Miranda van den Broek Judoka
Home
Judoka
Miranda van den Broek
Judo career
Miranda van den Broek
Country: Netherlands | Born: 11 May 1979 (44 years)
Judoka Miranda van den Broek won the World Cup Tallinn U78kg in 2006. The triple Dutch champion won 12 national medals and competed most with Claudia Zwiers U78kg. She won 8 World Cup medals in Den Bosch, Warsaw, Sofia, Leonding, Rotterdam, Munchen and victory in Tallinn. Club: Gerrit Bijsterbosch.

Fokelette Coelingh Judoka
Home
Judoka
Fokelette Coelingh
Judo career
Fokelette COELINGH
NED
JudoInside.com
Fokelette Coelingh
Country: Netherlands | Born: 16 May 1982 (41 years)
Fokelette Coelingh from the Netherlands took a medal 1 at Roland Cup International Bremen in 1998. She claimed a silver medal at Roland Cup International Bremen U17 in 1998. Fokelette ranked second at Dutch Championships U20 in 1999, 2000 and 2001. She secured a silver medal at Portuguese Open juniors Madeira in 1999. She captured a bronze medal at Belgian Ladies Open juniors Arlon in 1999 and she bagged a silver medal at Dutch Cadet Championships Maastricht in 1998.

Jordy Croese Judoka
Home
Judoka
Jordy Croese
Judo career
Jordy Croese
Country: Netherlands | Born: 7 July 1983 (40 years)
Judoka Jordy Croese claimed a gold medal at the A-Tournament U20 Göteborg in 2002. Croese trained at Dutch club Kenamju in Haarlem.

Arshak Dabaghian
Judo career
Arshak DABAGHIAN
NED
JudoInside.com
Arshak Dabaghian
Country: Netherlands | Born: 1 December 1974 (48 years)
Dutch judoka Arshak Dabaghian won the national title in 1998 U81kg. Originally from Armenia. became coach and club owner. Watch the full biography with all results, judo photos, videos and latest judo news at JudoInside.com

Bryan van Dijk Judoka
Home
Judoka
Bryan van Dijk
Judo career
Bryan van Dijk
Country: Netherlands | Born: 8 February 1981 (42 years)
Dutch judoka Bryan van Dijk won a European bronze medal in 2006 in Tampere U73kg. He won European junior bronze in 2000. Trained by Theo Meijer and stepped over to Kenamju. Suffered a shoulder injury. He won Super World Cup in Hamburg and Dutch Open in 2006 and Grand Prix in Tunis in 2009. Now enterpreneur in gadgets.
Judo career

Rianne van Dijken Judoka
Home
Judoka
Rianne van Dijken
Judo career
Rianne VAN DIJKEN
NED
JudoInside.com
Rianne van Dijken
Country: Netherlands | Born: 3 November 1984 (38 years)
Judoka Rianne van Dijken took a gold medal at the Dutch Team Championships Utrecht in 2004. She bagged a bronze medal at the Dutch Cadet Championships Maastricht in 1998. She claimed a gold medal at the Dutch Championships Mixed Teams in 2004. Rianne captured a silver medal at the Wilrijk International in 2003. She secured a bronze medal at the Dutch Open Juniors ‘s-Hertogenbosch U20 in 2003. She clinched a bronze medal at the International Tournament Venray U20 in 2003. Van Dijken won a silver medal at the Junior tournament Lommel in 2002 and Wilrijk in 2001.
Judo career

Denny Ebbers Judoka
Home
Judoka
Denny Ebbers
Judo career
Denny Ebbers
Country: Netherlands | Born: 17 July 1974 | Passed away: 22 July 2015 (41 years)
Dutch Olympian Denny Ebbers won a European bronze medal in 1995 in Birmingham. He won bronze at the European Junior Championships in 1993. The heavyweight competed at the 1996 Olympic Games. In 2009 the triple Dutch champion was diagnosed of cancer and passed away in 2015 losing his last fight.
Judo career

Guillaume Elmont Judoka
Home
Judoka
Guillaume Elmont
Judo career
Guillaume Elmont
Country: Netherlands | Born: 10 August 1981 (42 years)
Guillaume Elmont is 2005 World Champion and triple Olympic participant. Brother of Dex Elmont. Both from a judo family from Suriname. He won European Games bronze in 2015 in Baku, and 5 European medals in total. 2000 European junior Champion and won 11 national titles. He is physical coach at Ajax.
Judo career

Jenny Gal Judoka
Home
Judoka
Jenny Gal
Judo career
Jenny Gal
Country: Italy | Born: 2 November 1969 (53 years)
Jenny Gal is 1996 Olympic bronze medallist and 1995 World Championships finallist. Works as coach in Switzerland with her husband Giorgio Vismara. Sister of quadruple European Champion Jessica Gal. She has the responsibility of the U15 talents in Switzerland. Jenny was European champion in Birmingham in 1995 and claimed five European medals. She captured twelve World Cup gold medals including the Tournoi de Paris in 1989 for the Netherlands and 1999 for Italy. She lives with Giorgia Visamara as coaches in Switzerland.

Dennis van der Geest Judoka
Home
Judoka
Dennis van der Geest
Judo career
Dennis van der Geest
Country: Netherlands | Born: 27 June 1975 (48 years)
Dennis van der Geest is 2005 World Champion and 2004 Olympic bronze medallist. He won five World Championships medals (1997-2005) and two European titles in 2000 and 2002 among ten European medals. Dennis captured 11 gold medals at World Cups including the famous Tournoi de Paris in 1999. He claimed gold at the Dutch Open in Rotterdam. He became a successful entertainer and DJ and TV Presenter after he retired in 2008. Nickname: Woeste Willem. He was trained by Cor van der Geest, Herman Debrot, Ronald Joorse and Louis Wijdenbosch among others.

Elco van der Geest Judoka
Home
Judoka
Elco van der Geest
Judo career
Elco van der Geest
Country: Netherlands | Born: 4 May 1979 (44 years)
2002 and 2010 European Champion Elco van der Geest switched from Netherlands to Belgium in advance of the 2009 World Championships. He is the younger brother of Dennis van der Geest. Together they won the European title in 2002. Elco runs Kenamju supported by father Cor van der Geest. His judo examples are Toshihiko Koga and Wladimir Dgebouadze. Major World Cup wins: Rotterdam 2001, Rome 2002, Moscow 2002, Tunis GP 2009, Rio Grand Slam 2009 and 2010 and Paris Grand Slam 2010.

Kyra Gerritsjans Judoka

Judoka
Kyra Gerritsjans
Judo career
Kyra GERRITSJANS
NED
JudoInside.com
Kyra Gerritsjans
Country: Netherlands | Born: 28 March 1979 (44 years)
Dutch Judoka Kyra Gerritsjans from Groningen won the A-tournament Sofia 'Liberation' U63kg in 1998. She became national champion in 1997 and 2001 U63kg and won Dutch titles U17 and U20 years.

Deborah Gravenstijn Judoka
Home
Judoka
Deborah Gravenstijn
Judo career
Deborah Gravenstijn
Country: Netherlands | Born: 20 August 1974 (49 years)
Double Olympic medallist Deborah Gravenstijn is Olympic medallist in two categories in Athens 2004 (bronze) and finallist at Beijing 2008. She was in the final of the 2001 World Champinoships and took bronze in 2003 in Osaka. Deborah claimed five European medals and she claimed five victories at World Cups in Basel, Rome, Prague, Tallinn and Warsaw. She was able to collect 17 World Cup medals. She studied as Physiotherapist and has children with British coach Mark Earle.

Françoise Harteveld Judoka
Home
Judoka
Françoise Harteveld
Judo career
Françoise Harteveld
Country: Netherlands | Born: 26 March 1977 (46 years)
Judoka Françoise Harteveld was 1992 and 1995 European junior Champion. She became World Student Champion and Olympian. Franny was very successful as wrestler a after her judo career. Studied Human Resources Management & Personnel Policy. Started judo when she was 3 years old. She was European Champion in Oviedo in 1998 and claimed four European medals.She captured 21 medals including victories in Prague, Warsaw (2) and Rotterdam as some of her highlights. She was born in Maassluis and was coached by Rob Henneveld.

Miranda van Hengel Judoka
Home
Judoka
Miranda van Hengel
Judo career
Miranda VAN HENGEL
NED
JudoInside.com
Miranda van Hengel
Country: Netherlands | Born: 23 May 1979 (44 years)
Judoka Miranda van Hengel won five bronze medals in a row at Dutch Championships. She won various Dutch titles with her team Mahorokan and Top Judo West.

Winfried HOLTHUIZEN
NED
JudoInside.com
Winfried Holthuizen
Country: Netherlands | Born: 27 September 1973 (50 years)
Winfried Holthuizen started at hhis fifth at Hikari He won two national titles U60kg In total he won 8 national senior medals. His judo club was Sport-UNION Witten-Annen
